    {
      "_id": "gAoyIauEQ2VzhFrR",
      "name": "Brass Crossbow",
      "type": "weapon",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em><strong></strong> Ranged Weapon Attack:</em> +7 to hit, range 100/400 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> [[/damage 2d10 + @mod type=force average=true]] damage. The target also suffers one of the following effects of the orthon’s choice; the orthon can’t use the same effect two rounds in a row:</p><p><strong>&amp;Reference[acid]{Acid}.</strong> The target must make a [[/save con 17 format=long]], taking [[/damage 5d6 type=acid average=true]] damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p><strong>Blindness.</strong> The target takes [[/damage 1d10 type=radiant average=true]] damage. In addition, the target and each creature within 20 feet of it must succeed on a [[/save dex 17 format=long]] or be &amp;Reference[blinded]{blinded} until the end of the orthon’s next turn.</p><p><strong>Concussion.</strong> The target and each creature within 20 feet of it must make a [[/save con 17 format=long]], taking [[/damage 2d12 type=thunder average=true]] damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p><strong>Entanglement.</strong> The target must succeed on a [[/save dex 17 format=long]] or be &amp;Reference[restrained]{restrained} for 1 hour by strands of sticky webbing. The target can escape by taking an action to make a DC 17 &amp;Reference[str]{Strength} or &amp;Reference[dex]{Dexterity} check and succeeding.</p><p><strong>Paralysis.</strong> The target takes [[/damage 4d10 type=lightning average=true]] damage and must succeed on a [[/save con 17 format=long]] or be &amp;Reference[paralyzed]{paralyzed} for 1 minute. The &amp;Reference[paralyzed]{paralyzed} target can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p><p><strong>Tracking.</strong> For the next 24 hours, the orthon knows the direction and distance to the target, as long as it’s on the same plane of existence. If the target is on a different plane, the orthon knows which one, but not the exact location there.</p>\n</section>\nThe [[lookup @name]] attacks with its [[lookup @item.name]].\n</div>",
          "chat": ""
        },
